Drug repurposing (also known as drug repurposing, re-profiling, re-appointment or remedial modification) is the repurposing of an approved drug for the treatment of a disease or medical condition other than the one for which it was originally developed.
It is a system of scientific research that is currently being adopted to develop safe and effective COVID-19 treatments.
Other research instructions include the development of a COVID-19 vaccine and the well-being-related plasma transfusion. SARS-CoV-2 contains about 66 target proteins, each of which has multiple ligand binding sites.
